comments.body:
https://reviews.llvm.org/D155415 aims to address this issue. I tested local-exec initially, but recently the integrated assembler was made the default and I did not realize this issue before.

The correct behaviour is achieved with the above patch:
```
$ cat test.c
static __thread int x, y;
int main(void) {
  x = 1;
  return x + y;
}

$ clang -ftls-model=local-exec -m64 -pthreads test.c

$ ./a.out ; echo $?
1
```

